CatDescriptText: Mr. Theodore Ketchum, tailor at 1414 Wylie Avenue, was part of a man on the street column entitled "Amos 'n' Andy Television Show Offends Some, Pleases Others," published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 28, 1951, pg. 3
TitMainTitle: Portrait of tailor Theodore Ketchum, wearing eyeglasses, moustache, and light colored collared shirt with pens in left breast pocket, standing in interior of 1414 Wylie Avenue, with cash register and several articles of clothing on hangers
